        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-05-02T17:06:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m not sure how often we\u0027re doing Update(), but it seems to me that we could also pre-fetch details for all commits in range here.  My thinking is that it should be almost as fast to retrieve all of the commits as it is to retrieve a single one; pre-caching during Update() would help with latency in general.  We could optimize by only fetching details for those not already in the cache.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 117,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 117,
        "endChar": 55
      },
      "revId": "123f82eff35a638fac2f1048e95d54bfb2938034",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
